title: Overhauled how creates, updates, and deletes are sent back to Pinboard.  Now…
message:
Overhauled how creates, updates, and deletes are sent back to Pinboard.  Now using built in sync adapter functionality.  When a bookmark is updated now, the content provider triggers an upload only sync that syncs any pending changes to Pinboard.  This should result in more predictable operation during limited connectivity and low memory situations (issue that prompted change was for user who's bookmarks would not always save because the os would kill PinDroid too quickly after sharing a bookmark, which would kill the running async task as well).

title: Added preferences screen, wired up to existing settings menu button and added a…
message: Added preferences screen, wired up to existing settings menu button and added a link from the account management screen.  Only setting currently is a checkbox to allow notifications on new inbox links.

title: As promised, sign in experience for oauth accounts is even more improved. …
message: As promised, sign in experience for oauth accounts is even more improved.  Instead of bouncing the verification code callback through an external site that redirects to a url, I am just intercepting the callback redirect and getting the code directly.

title: Improved the sign in experience for oauth.  Instead of taking the user to a page…
message: Improved the sign in experience for oauth.  Instead of taking the user to a page and asking them to retype the verification code, they are now redirected to a page hosted on droidlicious.webs.com that redirects it back to a certain url that the app picks up and reads the verification code from.  I may be able to do this without the redirect, but it works for now.

title: Split the new account authentication screen into two views, one to ask for the…
message: Split the new account authentication screen into two views, one to ask for the account type (delicious or oauth) and then either the username/password screen (for delcious) or straight to the webview for yahoo authentication (for oauth).  Also had to add a dummy call to the recent posts api to get the username for oauth accounts.
